TI  - Antimicrobial stewardship programs in intensive care units: a systematic review
AB  - Background: Antimicrobial resistance is a growing threat in ICU settings. This systematic review evaluates the effectiveness of antimicrobial stewardship programs (ASPs) in reducing resistance rates and improving patient outcomes in adult ICU patients. Methods: We searched PubMed, Embase, and Cochrane Library for RCTs and observational studies comparing ASPs with standard care. Results: 23 studies met inclusion criteria. ASPs significantly reduced antimicrobial consumption and resistance rates without increasing mortality.
